  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "Sport climbing crag near Flaten. This crag has been rediscovered. The old Stockholm guidebook gives the names and grades of the original routes, all of which were climbed without artificial aids for the weak-minded... In 2009, the Bolt Committee gave the crag a thorough overhaul, including installing anchors above most routes and cleaning sections that had previously become overgrown with moss. Beware of mosquitoes.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:ekstubbeberget"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekstubbeberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A sport climbing crag near Flaten. This crag has been rediscovered. The old Stockholm guidebook lists the original routes’ names and grades, all of which were climbed without artificial aids for the feeble-minded... In 2009, the crag was given a thorough overhaul by the Bolt Committee, which, among other things, installed anchors above most routes and brushed the sections that had previously become covered in moss. Beware of mosquitoes.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekstubbeberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekstubbeberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "It is just as easy to get there by car as by public transport. Take bus 811 or 816 from Gullmarsplan, or bus 401 from Slussen (which does not run very often). Get off at Flatenbadet and follow Flatenvägen to the bridge over Tyresövägen. Just before the bridge, turn right down a gated road signposted to the race track. Pass a model car racing circuit on the left, turn right by the buildings (MHF) and head towards the older race track. Pass behind the grandstand on the right-hand side of the track and take the broad path straight down towards the water. On reaching the water, turn left onto the small path and continue for about 100–200 metres. You should now have the crag directly ahead of you.\n\nIf arriving by car, park on the road leading down to the race track, before the barrier, unless you want your car locked in when the radio-controlled car drivers finish for the day. Alternatively, park at Flatenbadet.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekstubbeberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder": {
